        "header": "4Method",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.14660/2607.14660v1/img/new_tpad.png",
                "caption": "Figure 4:Overview of Token-Level Prompt Activation Decoding (TPAD).\nGiven a fixed forced-choice prompt, the MLLM processes a concatenated token sequence consisting of the prompt and video frame representations.\nFor each frame, the hidden state of its final token is projected via the language modeling head to obtain the probability of issuing an alert (option A).\nTPAD enables efficient, context-aware alert detection for offline models through a single forward pass.\nIn this example, an alert is triggered only at T = 58.00s.",
                "position": 664
            }
        ]
